This paper is about training a task-completion dialogue agent using reinforcement learning and planning. It involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning (DL) and RL, which are also associated with "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and simulation, which are associated with "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) and "Human-Computer Interaction" (cs.HC) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses more on NLP and ML techniques, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.SI, and cs.HC.
